                            <comment id="14167" author="simmonsja" created="Wed, 11 May 2011 08:02:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello. I have been working on SuSE 11.1 and SuSE11-SP1 support as well. Currently cray sea star requires the pre service pack SuSE  11 version which I have resurrected. The cray SIO nodes need to support local attached disk so I have now two SuSE versions for ldiskfs. So I&apos;m wondering if I use this LU or should I create a new one?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
